name:
Photon 1.21 
(c) 2022 ermouth 

Run attachment `index.html` to start Photon. 

See https://github.com/ermouth/couch-photon 
repo for more details.
versions:
## 1.21.9

Fixed multiple issues with grid views: columns are now 
derived correctly on slower machines, don’t ‘stick’ 
on view switch, better behave when switched to show 
reduce results.

## 1.21.7

New [Add view…] button in the DB docs/view panel. Opens 
a dialog to create JS, Erlang or Mango index in a 
current DB.

Fixed invalid `partial_filter_selector` location in the 
default Mango index.

Code editor for view indices and Mango stuff is now limited 
in width, so more space for query results.

Fixed issues with switching view after performing [Save as…] 
in view code editor.

## 1.21.6

Most inputs received autocomplete=off attribute. Viewindex
grid rebuilds when reduce switches, to better fit different 
structure of map and reduce responses.

Grid selectors like `.value.*.somefield /list` now work not 
only if .value is an array, but with objects as well. Very 
handy for reducers which return objects.

User info popup now has Forget viewstates command. The cmd
clears local state cache of columns settings for visited 
views, and also clears local cache keeping expanded/collapsed 
state of branches in visited docs.

## 1.21.2

New feature: DB conflicts list for CouchDB 2.3+ (a simple 
Mango query under the hood). Also Mango qry result rows with 
`_id` field now have links to parent documents.

Default view mode is now Grid. Reduce selector is now visible 
in that mode.

A lot of minor tune-ups for dark theme here and there.

DB group members in the DB list are now indented.

Links to design doc attachments in JSON editor no more
have escaped slashes in `_design/` prefix.

## 1.20.7

Fixed invalid tabstrip colors for inherited light theme. 
Several small dark theme tweaks. Slightly improved JSON 
coloring.

## 1.20.5

No more browser tab stalls in Chrome when undumping zips
containing tens of thousands small docs.

## 1.20.3

A lot of minor dark theme related UI tweaks here and there.

## 1.20.2

New feature: dark theme, controlled in Photon config.

## 1.19.10

Mango validator now catches invalid/misspelled $ operators.

## 1.19.9

Added response size/duration indicator at the bottom of 
view results. Some refactoring, moving from ES5 to ES6.

## 1.19.8

Fixed doc clone dlg, copying a design doc is now ok.

Photon default repo URL was changed, updates are now delivered 
strictly over https.

## 1.19.7

Improved DB list group segmentation.

## 1.19.6

Fixed DB info rolldown z-index issues.

## 1.19.5

Added horizontal rulers to DB groups, for better group demarcation. 
Switching to grid view now tries to guess most relevant columns.
Minor Linux FF-related fixes.

## 1.19.2

New feature: expandable DB auto-groups. Grouping makes Photon
comfortable for nodes with thousands DBs. Grouping mode and limits 
are tunable in Photon settings.

Doc list for `_users` doesn’t read security descriptors for all
DBs any more, only first 100 of not present are read.

## 1.18

Mostly UI fixes and performance improvements. Starred DBs show
security and size regardless of Photon config.

## 1.17

Added Mango syntax validator into query editor. Added
Ping session config option. 

CouchDB 3.2 related: incompatible CSP config handling.

Added Ctrl-S and Ctrl-Z (Cmd-S and Cmd-Z for Mac) global keyboard 
shortcuts for config, doc and attachment editors.

Compatibility with old IEs is no more maintained.

## 1.16

Added Undo history panel into doc and config editors. The panel 
is a list of all json changes, and in most cases allows to 
undo json tree changes out of order.

## 1.15

Added left panel / top bar switch to match wide monitors better. 
Vertical panel only available for 1420px+ wide screens.

Max 15 tabs message removed, older tabs are auto-closed if needed.

Bucket stats numbers in DB list are clickable and show DB info.

Added typecast ` /cast` modifiers for selectors in grid view.

Added [Clone...] button in doc editor; basically `Save as...`.

Added [../] button in views, which opens bucket root doc list.

## 1.14

Added grid (table) representation mode for docs lists, view and 
Mango queries. Tables are copy/pastable to Excel. 

Added Include docs option for `/_all_docs` view, it is turned on 
automatically for grid view mode.

Views now memoize their particular source code editor state, as 
well as reduce level and grid settings.

## 1.12

Added ZIP dump/restore. A [Delete DB] dlg now offers to re-create 
DB(s) after deletion. Several JSON editor fixes and improvements. 
Task list grouping improved. 

TT Mono font excluded from the Photon package. 

## 1.11

Added `/_changes` feed view, added compound index stats for 
ddocs view.

## 1.10

Added index stats for each ddoc in ddocs view; also a lot of 
slight UI improvements.

## 1.9

Added: group DB sync; Couch perf test; CouchDB v3 support. 

## 1.8

Improved JSON editor, added `/_stats` graphs.

## 1.7

Added structured diff for doc revisions.

## 1.6

New features: editor for text-based attachments and doc purge. 
DB view received `db/_design_docs` and `db/_local_docs` modes.

## 1.4

Added access restrictions, Photon no more starts without 
authorization.

## 1.2

Added in-place editors for Erlang, JS and Mango view syntax.

## 0.9.99

More or less usable version with all basic features. March, 2018.
